==English==

===Etymology===
From {{compound|back|lash}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈbækˌlæʃ/}}
* {{audio|en-us-backlash.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|es}}

# A sudden backward motion.
# A [[reaction]], [[objection]] or [[outcry]], especially of a [[violent]] or [[abrupt]] nature.
#: The public '''backlash''' to the proposal was quick and insistent.
# {{context|mechanics|lang=en}} The [[distance]] through which one part of connected machinery, as a [[wheel]], [[piston]], or [[screw]], can be moved without moving the connected parts, resulting from [[loose]]ness in fitting or from wear.
# The [[jarring]] or [[reflex]] motion caused in badly fitting machinery by irregularities in velocity or a reverse of motion.

